headline: White House considers antitrust probe into homebuilders, Bloomberg News reports
summary: Feb 6 (Reuters) - Trump administration officials are exploring opening an antitrust investigation into U.S. homebuilders as the White House ramps up efforts to address the housing affordability crisis

headline: Homebuilder stocks fall after potential antitrust probe report
summary: Investing.com -- Shares of major U.S. homebuilders fell Friday following a Bloomberg report that the White House is considering launching an antitrust investigation into the industry amid concerns about housing affordability.

headline: A Key Takeaway From Earnings Season: Signs of Consumer Weakness
summary: Earnings season is more than halfway over, and a clear laggard is emerging: companies that sell non-essential items to consumers.  A high ratio of companies—38%—have also missed consensus earnings forecasts.  The sector covers a broad swathe of the economy, encompassing a range of companies from Amazon and DoorDash to Tractor Supply and Marriott.

headline: Del Webb Breaks Ground on Two New Resort-Style Communities in the Columbus Area
summary: COLUMBUS, Ohio, February 06, 2026--Del Webb, the nation’s leading builder of active-adult communities, has officially broken ground on the Welcome Centers and model parks in two resort-style communities in the Columbus market. The ceremonial events at Del Webb Maygrass in Plain City and Del Webb Explore at Northstar in Sunbury mark a major milestone in the brand’s Midwest expansion, bringing world-class amenities, once associated primarily with Sunbelt locations, to Central Ohio homebuyers.

headline: How The PulteGroup (PHM) Story Is Evolving As Fair Value And Street Views Shift
summary: Why the PulteGroup Fair Value View Has Shifted The fair value estimate for PulteGroup has moved slightly, from about US$139.31 to about US$140.92 per share, reflecting updated assumptions around how the story could play out from here. Behind that change, the discount rate is now about 8.67% instead of about 8.62%, and revenue is now modeled at about 2.31% growth rather than a 1.16% decline, as analysts weigh a generally constructive tone against ongoing caution on housing demand and building...
